    "We trained a classical ML model using randomly chosen values of the parameter vector x = {J ij }.",
    "For each parameter vector of random couplings sampled uniformly from [0, 2], we approximated the ground state using the same method as in 36, namely with the density-matrix renormalization group (DMRG) 64 based on matrix product states (MPS) 65.",
